  "notes": [
    {
      "id": "1cc26f45-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralTitle",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 0,
      "content": "IMPORTANT MAJOR INFORMATION",
      "contentHtml": null
    },
    {
      "id": "28c26f45-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralText",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 1,
      "content": "Asian Religions majors choose their main language concentration in Chinese, Japanese, Korean, South Asian, or Southeast Asian languages, while simultaneously acquiring broad cultural competence by taking courses in religion from at least four countries or areas across Asia. This provides them with a combination of strong language skills and the ability to analyze and interpret multiple religious traditions in a part of the world where religion still matters enormously in many facets of life. Listed below are the lower division preparation information courses for the major. To be considered for this major, you must complete the following courses by the end of spring before transfer: One year of college level coursework in an Asian language OR At least one year of high school in which the primary language of instruction was an Asian language. Completion of two years of college level foreign language courses is STRONGLY RECOMMENDED . A placement exam is required for all language majors regardless of credits earned in lower division language courses. All courses must be taken for a letter grade. For more information regarding this major and UCLA's transfer selection process, visit https:// www.alc.ucla.edu and https:// admission.ucla.edu . PLEASE NOTE: the community college courses listed below have been approved to satisfy the preparation for this major at UCLA, but they may not be exact equivalents of the UCLA courses listed.",
      "contentHtml": "<p>Asian Religions majors choose their main language concentration in Chinese, Japanese, Korean, South Asian, or Southeast Asian languages, while simultaneously acquiring broad cultural competence by taking courses in religion from at least four countries or areas across Asia. This provides them with a combination of strong language skills and the ability to analyze and interpret multiple religious traditions in a part of the world where religion still matters enormously in many facets of life.</p><p><br></p><p>Listed below are the lower division preparation information courses for the major.</p><p><br></p><p>To be considered for this major, you must complete the following courses by the end of spring before transfer:</p><ul><li>One year of college level coursework in an Asian language OR</li><li>At least one year of high school in which the primary language of instruction was an Asian language.</li></ul><p>Completion of two years of college level foreign language courses is <strong>STRONGLY RECOMMENDED</strong>.</p><p>A placement exam is required for all language majors regardless of credits earned in lower division language courses.</p><p>All courses must be taken for a letter grade.</p><p><br></p><p>For more information regarding this major and UCLA's transfer selection process, visit <u style=\"color: rgb(41, 98, 255);\">https://</u><a href=\"http://www.alc.ucla..edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">www.alc.ucla.edu</a> and <u style=\"color: rgb(41, 98, 255);\">https://</u><a href=\"http://www.admission.ulca.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">admission.ucla.edu</a>.</p><p><br></p><p>PLEASE NOTE: the community college courses listed below have been approved to satisfy the preparation for this major at UCLA, but they may not be exact equivalents of the UCLA courses listed.</p>"
    }
